<protolog id="rid.6099_nm.10241" type="description" xmlns="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog file:/C:/NamesforLife/workspace/namesforlife-schema/protolog.xsd"><organism doi="10.1601/nm.10241" rank="genus">Meganema</organism><reference id="rid.6099"><citation citation-type="journal"><authors><person-name><surname>Thomsen</surname><given-names>T.R.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Blackall</surname><given-names>L.L.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>de Muro</surname><given-names>M.A.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Nielsen</surname><given-names>J.L.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Nielsen</surname><given-names>P.H.</given-names></person-name></authors><article-title>Meganema perideroedes gen. nov., sp. nov., a filamentous alphaproteobacterium from activated sludge.</article-title><year>2006</year><volume>56</volume><issue>8</issue><fpage>1865</fpage><lpage>1868</lpage><source id="117">International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology</source><abbrev>Int J Syst Evol Microbiol</abbrev><issn>1466-5026</issn><essn>1466-5034</essn><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1099/ijs.0.02916-0</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">16902022</pub-id></citation></reference><content><p class="title"><s>Description of <em>Meganema</em> gen. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><em>Meganema</em> (Me.ga.ne′ma. Gr. nom. neut. adj. <em>mega</em> big; Gr. nom. neut. n. <em>nema</em> thread; N.L. neut. n. <em>Meganema</em> large thread-like micro-organism).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Filamentous bacteria.</s><s>Cells stain Gram-negative and contain some Neisser-positive granules and PHB granules.</s><s>The major quinone is Q-10.</s><s>Fatty acid profiles are dominated by C<sub>18 : 1</sub><em>ω</em>7<em>c</em>; characteristic hydroxy acids are C<sub>14 : 0</sub> 3-OH and C<sub>18 : 0</sub> 3-OH. <em>Meganema</em> belongs to the <em>Alphaproteobacteria</em> and the type species is <em>Meganema perideroedes</em>.</s></p></content></protolog>